CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 7, 1962, pg. 2 reads: "Auxiliary of Guardsmen Legion - Shown above are some of the many delegates to the national convention of the Legion of Guardsmen, meeting this week in Pittsburgh, with headquarters at Hotel Webster Hall. Members of the women's auxiliary are, left to right, seated: Patricia Wilson, senior vice president of Parkersburg, W.Va.; Margaret F. Cobbs, national president; Emma Alford, national secretary, and Evelyn Beighorn, national junior vice president.  Standing: Betty Burdick, Providence, R.I., national treasurer; Udell Stoddard, Bethel, Vt.; Cassie Mills, Claremont, N.H.; Genevieve Omerberg, Parkersburg, W.Va.; Helen Wilson, Parkersburg, W. Va.; Hilda Silva, New York City, and Edna Riley, Canton, Ohio. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of eleven members of the Legion of Guardsmen Women's Auxiliary, from left, seated: Patricia Wilson, Margaret F. Cobbs, Emma Alford, and Evelyn Beighorn; standing: Betty Burdick, Udell Stoddard, Cassie Mills, Genevieve Omerberg, Helen Wilson, Hilda Silva, and Edna Riley, posed in Webster Hall during national convention
